75
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:29,880
You're stepping on it!

76
00:04:29,950 --> 00:04:33,300
Huh? Oh no! I'm sorry!

77
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:34,670
I'm sorry.

78
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:37,710
We don't get along at all.

79
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:40,130
Well, but you had a good time, right?

80
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:42,250
What to do?

81
00:04:42,670 --> 00:04:45,670
The two of us are completely different.

82
00:04:46,410 --> 00:04:48,450
I'm the athletic type from Naniwa

83
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:50,863
and Soga-san is the cultural type

84
00:04:50,894 --> 00:04:51,894
from Tokyo.

85
00:04:52,410 --> 00:04:53,780
Maybe one day, Soga-san will

86
00:04:53,970 --> 00:04:55,175
start making al ajillo

87
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,548
with a takoyaki maker.

88
00:04:56,580 --> 00:04:58,240
I'll definitely get mad!

89
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,511
What does he think

90
00:04:59,543 --> 00:05:00,894
a takoyaki maker is for?

91
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,110
Well, but it won't happen.

92
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:06,400
Oh?

93
00:05:07,310 --> 00:05:08,240
Takoyaki...

94
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:10,150
for me and Soga-san,

95
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,340
it holds a special memory.

96
00:05:17,710 --> 00:05:19,900
Having those roots connecting us

97
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:24,780
is my salvation.

98
00:05:36,210 --> 00:05:37,452
I saw online that you can make

99
00:05:37,477 --> 00:05:38,772
al ajillo with a takoyaki maker.

100
00:05:40,139 --> 00:05:41,150
Now that I think about it,

101
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:42,800
it's the perfect shape for it, huh?

102
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,640
Um, Soga-san...

103
00:05:47,610 --> 00:05:48,160
Huh?

104
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:50,090
Making al ajillo

105
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:52,450
with a takoyaki maker...

106
00:06:03,370 --> 00:06:05,370
That's quite a cool idea, isn't it?

107
00:06:08,030 --> 00:06:08,760
Geez...

108
00:06:09,030 --> 00:06:10,770
I didn't come up with it myself.

109
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,597
Well, I was really tired

110
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:14,543
of regular takoyaki,

111
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,880
so al ajillo is a good choice.

112
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:19,140
Yeah.

113
00:06:20,090 --> 00:06:21,440
I'm glad you liked it.

114
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,820
- Oh, I'll get some drinks.
- Sure.

115
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:34,610
The soul of an Osaka person,

116
00:06:35,850 --> 00:06:37,830
I sold it out.

117
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:41,900
Here.

118
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:44,740
Ah, thank you.

119
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:47,550
And this.

120
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:48,780
Huh?

121
00:06:49,990 --> 00:06:51,810
Post-Impressionist art exhibition.

122
00:06:52,270 --> 00:06:53,960
Would you like to go together?

123
00:06:58,230 --> 00:07:00,170
Yes, let's go!

124
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,141
Wow. I bet there are as many postboxes

125
00:07:05,166 --> 00:07:06,922
as there are countries.

126
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:09,400
- Huh?
- Huh?

127
00:07:11,460 --> 00:07:12,130
Postboxes?

128
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:14,480
(Encyclopedia of Modern Art)

129
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:16,490
It's no good.

130
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,670
Nothing enters my head at all.

131
00:07:21,796 --> 00:07:23,189
(Tamae)

132
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:25,000
- Don't say strange things.
- That's hilarious.

133
00:07:26,020 --> 00:07:28,380
Sakae-kun!

134
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:29,520
Sakae-kun!

135
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,477
What's with that

136
00:07:31,502 --> 00:07:33,143
gloomy face since earlier?

137
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,625
Yeah, you're ruining

138
00:07:34,650 --> 00:07:36,399
the sake and snacks for us.

139
00:07:36,470 --> 00:07:37,240
Right?

140
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:39,580
- I'm sorry.
- It's fine.

141
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,600
Hey.

142
00:07:43,275 --> 00:07:44,750
Oh, Kaname?

143
00:07:45,130 --> 00:07:46,390
Hey. Just by yourself?

144
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,070
Good evening.

145
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:50,950
Nice to meet you.

146
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:54,790
Ah, you're Kazuyo-chan, right?

147
00:07:55,836 --> 00:07:57,590
I've heard about you.

148
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,164
Apparently, you're a beautiful

149
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:00,406
regular customer now.

150
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:02,600
Cut it out. Come on, let's drink.

151
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,320
This way.

152
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,250
Huh? Wait. What?

153
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:07,030
A bottle of barley soju, please!

154
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,010
Let's drink.

155
00:08:08,490 --> 00:08:10,460
- A bottle of soju, please.
- Sure.

156
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:12,110
- Two more of this snack, please.
- Sure.

157
00:08:13,540 --> 00:08:15,780
Umm, Kaname-san, you

158
00:08:16,248 --> 00:08:17,381
have been friends with Sakae-san

159
00:08:17,406 --> 00:08:18,585
since childhood, right?

160
00:08:18,990 --> 00:08:19,960
Well, yeah.

161
00:08:19,990 --> 00:08:21,770
In that case, I'd like to know.

162
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:25,640
What kind of person is Sakae-san's type?

163
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,770
Type?

164
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:30,630
- What do you mean...
- Or rather,

165
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:34,800
is Sakae-san dating anyone right now?

166
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:39,140
- Well, I don't think so.
- Is that so?

167
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:45,140
- That's a relief.
- Welcome.

168
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:46,527
Sakae-san is good at

169
00:08:46,552 --> 00:08:48,160
sports in general, right?

170
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:49,650
Well, yes.

171
00:08:49,980 --> 00:08:52,440
I also love physical exercise.

172
00:08:52,839 --> 00:08:53,790
I'm taking Muay Thai lessons

173
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:56,130
three times a week.

174
00:08:56,670 --> 00:08:57,780
Oh, really?

175
00:08:58,470 --> 00:09:00,120
I think it's important to

176
00:09:00,145 --> 00:09:02,285
share common interests, right?

177
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:11,760
You see...

178
00:09:19,010 --> 00:09:20,560
No, sorry. It's nothing.

179
00:09:20,690 --> 00:09:21,080
Hmm?

180
00:09:22,690 --> 00:09:23,240
I knew it,

181
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:26,090
he likes it, right? Is it exciting?

182
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:28,330
We need to try it together.

183
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:32,620
Kazuyo-chan likes you 100%.

184
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:38,240
Well...

185
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,565
I was wondering why she came

186
00:09:40,589 --> 00:09:41,776
to my shop so frequently.

187
00:09:43,170 --> 00:09:44,323
Shouldn't you tell her that

188
00:09:44,332 --> 00:09:45,940
you are not interested in women?

189
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:47,610
But...

190
00:09:48,082 --> 00:09:50,662
it's not like she told me directly.

191
00:09:52,330 --> 00:09:53,710
Well, that's true.

192
00:09:54,890 --> 00:09:57,150
When the right moment comes,

193
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,110
I'll talk to her properly.

194
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:00,660
Yeah.

195
00:10:01,570 --> 00:10:02,610
You're right.

196
00:10:03,310 --> 00:10:04,080
But...

197
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,366
hearing that it's important to share

198
00:10:06,391 --> 00:10:07,452
common interests...

199
00:10:09,590 --> 00:10:10,760
Makes my ears hurt.

200
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,936
Did something happen

201
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,171
with Soga-san again?

202
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:18,147
We went to an art exhibition together

203
00:10:18,163 --> 00:10:19,125
the other day.

204
00:10:19,150 --> 00:10:20,663
After looking at many paintings,

205
00:10:20,679 --> 00:10:21,925
he asked for my thoughts.

206
00:10:21,950 --> 00:10:24,000
Oh. What did you say?

207
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:26,790
At any rate,

208
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:28,680
I just said,

209
00:10:29,490 --> 00:10:30,930
'It's deep, ' for every painting.

210
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,780
How shallow.

211
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:34,962
I ended up buying a clear file

212
00:10:34,987 --> 00:10:36,884
at the gift shop in front of Soga-san.

213
00:10:38,230 --> 00:10:40,450
Well, it's definitely your style.

214
00:10:41,730 --> 00:10:43,136
When you like someone, you tend to

215
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,823
conform completely to their preferences.

216
00:10:45,550 --> 00:10:46,910
Are you talking about Mizuki?

217
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:48,900
Well...

218
00:10:52,540 --> 00:10:53,880
Mizuki, huh?

219
00:11:05,710 --> 00:11:07,930
Well, that guy was a total mess.

220
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:09,913
I know Mizuki and Soga-san

221
00:11:09,938 --> 00:11:11,069
are different.

222
00:11:11,939 --> 00:11:13,616
But I'm a little worried that you'll be

223
00:11:13,648 --> 00:11:15,577
pushed around and get hurt

224
00:11:15,602 --> 00:11:16,900
like you did back then.

225
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,702
Considering the other person

226
00:11:19,726 --> 00:11:20,725
is important,

227
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,820
- but it's okay to be a little selfish.
- Don't worry.

228
00:11:24,180 --> 00:11:26,360
I am not in love with Soga-san.

229
00:11:27,180 --> 00:11:28,960
I've decided to be friends with him.

230
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:32,420
Even then...

231
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:33,691
I can't deny that

232
00:11:33,716 --> 00:11:35,098
I'm being pushed around.

233
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:37,540
But I won't be hurt by that.

234
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:44,810
- Kazuyo.
- Hmm?

235
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,730
- Tawarauchi-san?
- Please check it when you're free.

236
00:11:46,730 --> 00:11:47,770
- Sure.
- Yes, thank you.

237
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:51,160
I'm sorry, even though it's my job.

238
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:54,160
It's fine. I'll handle it quickly.

239
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,100
- Kanda-san
- Thank you.

240
00:11:55,441 --> 00:11:58,040
- seems more enthusiastic lately.
- Sure, it's fine.

241
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,420
Yes.

242
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:01,820
I need to learn from her.

243
00:12:02,190 --> 00:12:05,080
Oh, Soga-kun, you're doing great.

244
00:12:05,180 --> 00:12:06,750
Look, the other day...

245
00:12:07,264 --> 00:12:08,861
when you were invited to that party

246
00:12:08,902 --> 00:12:10,208
at the client's place.

247
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,170
Well, I just got carried away...

248
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:14,680
This looks really cool.

249
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:15,070
No, no.

250
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,560
Oh, but

251
00:12:17,530 --> 00:12:18,430
it was a lot of fun.

252
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:19,340
Oh.

253
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,500
That's good.

254
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:23,393
In the end, it's about relationships

255
00:12:23,417 --> 00:12:25,683
between people in the Reiwa era.

256
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:27,210
You must enjoy everything you do.

257
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:28,720
Indeed.

258
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,010
However, well,

259
00:12:31,026 --> 00:12:33,026
there are many sorts of cases.

260
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:35,281
Building relationships

261
00:12:35,306 --> 00:12:36,922
outside of work is important,

262
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:38,220
but even with our clients,

263
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,490
they're not always good people.

264
00:12:47,595 --> 00:12:48,360
Sakae-kun...

265
00:12:48,650 --> 00:12:51,280
Sakae-kun, do you like squash?

266
00:12:51,610 --> 00:12:52,990
Squash?

267
00:12:54,730 --> 00:12:56,000
I like it!

268
00:12:56,490 --> 00:12:58,400
I used to play squash.

269
00:12:59,668 --> 00:13:01,263
If you're interested, how about playing

270
00:13:01,279 --> 00:13:02,372
together sometime?

271
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:03,290
Huh?

272
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:04,720
Huh?

273
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:08,380
Huh?

274
00:13:10,325 --> 00:13:13,580
Soga-san, do you play squash?

275
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:14,910
Yes.

276
00:13:15,310 --> 00:13:17,690
Well, I just dabble in it.

277
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:19,550
What's with that?

278
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:21,550
He should have told me sooner!

279
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:27,820
By all means! Let's do it!

280
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:37,070
There it is!

281
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:45,080
Now that you mention it,

282
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:48,200
squash would suit Soga-san, wouldn't it?

283
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,390
Sakae-kun!

284
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:55,560
Soga-san!

285
00:13:56,330 --> 00:13:57,160
Sakae-kun!

286
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:04,700
